  "text_preview": "\"first\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► FIRST : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"first\" Note: There are many \"right\" versions of this sign. General sign for first (the most flexible). Meanings: \"First of all\" \"Original\" \"Prototype\" This is a variation of the same sign. Notice how the index finger moves past the thumb instead of stopping at the thumb like in the other variation. Both ways are okay. I suggest you do the first variation, but that doesn't make this version wrong. See below for even more ways to sign \"first.\" This version brings the index finger to the thumb where it makes contact but doesn't go past. Another version of \"first\" And yet another version of \"first\" First as in \"the first one in a series.\" First place"
}
